---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Aerospace engineering student at Florida Tech. North Attleboro to Melbourne.">
  <main class="about-main">

    <header class="about-header">
      <p class="label" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">About</p>
      <h1>The mountain only asks:<br /><em>will you keep climbing?</em></h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-body">

      <p>
        I have two callings: mountains and cities. I have spent time in New York, Boston,
        Philadelphia, DC, San Francisco, Denver, Los Angeles — drawn to the noise, the density,
        the feeling that something is always being built or torn down. And then I disappear
        into the White Mountains or the Rockies and remember that none of it matters as much
        as I think it does. The mountain doesn't care where you went to school, how many views
        your writing has, how many papers you've published, or how organized your Notion is.
        It only asks one thing.
      </p>

      <p>
        I grew up in North Attleboro, Massachusetts — got there in fourth grade after moving
        around enough to understand that adaptation isn't optional, it's just life. I played
        baseball and football until I realized football was taking too many of the brain cells
        I was planning to use for other things. So I gave it up. One brain. Better make it count.
      </p>

      <p>
        I chose Florida Tech because I wanted to get away and start my own version of things.
        Not running from anything. Just ready to find out what I was made of when nobody who
        knew me was watching. Aerospace engineering felt like the right kind of hard — the kind
        that would force me to grow whether I wanted to or not.
      </p>

      <p>
        I think about engineering the way some people think about philosophy. Not just rockets
        and software — engineering is a way of confronting assumptions, a discipline of learning
        from failure fast enough to stay in the game. I used to be afraid of failure. Now I
        think it's probably the fastest teacher available, and I actively try to be the least
        experienced person in the room as often as possible. That's not humility for its own sake.
        That's how you close the gap.
      </p>

      <p>
        There is structure within the chaos. The research, the finance modeling, the writing,
        the coffee — it all has a logic behind it, even when any given moment feels like too
        many things at once. I work at Starbucks because service is in my family's background,
        because I genuinely care about the person on the other side of the counter, and because
        I love cold brew: simple, a little bitter, occasionally misunderstood. That's probably
        an accurate self-description.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside of all of it, I write. Poetry, essays, brain dumps at 1am about being a student
        and what it means to be a person still becoming one. I write about the hustle and the
        loneliness and the strange beauty of caring deeply about things that most people don't
        think about. I write because the technical world needs somewhere to be honest about
        itself, and I need somewhere to be honest about me.
      </p>

      <p>
        What I'm trying to figure out right now is how to take it easy. How to sit with a
        thunderstorm or the smell of something good without immediately turning it into a
        problem to solve. I'm wired for systems and infrastructure and what comes next — and
        I'm learning, slowly, that the small things are not a distraction from the work.
        They might be the point.
      </p>

    </section>

    <blockquote class="about-quote">
      "The mountain does not care where you went to school, how many views your writing has,
      how many papers you have published, or how organized your Notion is.
      The mountain only asks: will you keep climbing."
    </blockquote>

    <div class="about-photos">
      <figure class="about-photo young">
        <img src="/photos/young-parker.jpg" alt="Parker, younger, on the subway" />
        <figcaption>North Attleboro era.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="about-photo current">
        <img src="/photos/river-portrait.jpg" alt="Parker by the river" />
        <figcaption>Melbourne, FL.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <section class="principles">
      <h2>How I operate</h2>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li><em>Build before you feel ready.</em></li>
        <li><em>Document the mess.</em></li>
        <li><em>Be the least experienced person in the room as often as possible.</em></li>
        <li><em>Failure is the fastest teacher.</em></li>
        <li><em>Discipline is not aesthetics — it is returning.</em></li>
        <li><em>The field notes matter.</em></li>
        <li><em>The small things are not a distraction. They might be the point.</em></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-quick">
      <div class="quick-grid">
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Education</span>
          <p>B.S. Aerospace Engineering<br />Florida Institute of Technology<br />Expected May 2028 · GPA 3.3</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Research</span>
          <p>Aerospace Systems and Propulsion Lab<br />ROS · Gazebo · Foxglove · MCAP<br />SmartSignals Edge-AI Traffic Systems</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Writing</span>
          <p>Ground Control on Substack<br />Poetry, essays, field notes<br />The human condition, mostly</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Located</span>
          <p>Melbourne, FL<br />From North Attleboro, MA<br />Born in Providence, RI</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-main {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .about-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .about-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.9;
    color: var(--dim);
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .about-body p strong { color: var(--text); }
  .about-body p em    { color: var(--text); font-style: italic; }
  .about-body p a     { color: var(--accent); }

  /* Pull quote */
  .about-quote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Photos */
  .about-photos {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .about-photo {
    margin: 0;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 8px 8px 28px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-photo.young {
    width: 180px;
    transform: rotate(-2deg);
  }

  .about-photo.current {
    width: 220px;
    transform: rotate(1.5deg);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-photo img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 220px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-photo.young img { height: 240px; }

  figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Principles */
  .principles {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .principles h2 { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  .principles-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .principles-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .principles-list li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* Quick facts */
  .about-quick { margin-top: 1rem; }

  .quick-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .quick-item p {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
